# Fluff Date: 2026-02-15 19:10:51
overview:<p>The Bane, known to Inner Sphere forces by the reporting name Kraken, is a hundred-ton Clan assault BattleMech first constructed in 2827. Based on plans for a Star League prototype that never reached the production stage, the design was brought to fruition during the early years of the Clans following Operation Klondike. Originally serving as a key assault 'Mech across numerous Clan toumans, the Bane was gradually relegated to second-line and garrison duties with the advent of the OmniMech.</p><p>Despite this diminished status, the design remained a principal component of many Clan defensive formations, particularly within Clan Jade Falcon. The Falcon scientists' continued interest in the platform transformed it into a test bed for experimental technology, ensuring the venerable Bane saw more innovation and variation across its history than virtually any other Falcon second-line design.</p>

capabilities:<p>The Bane's primary strength lies in its role as a long-range, direct-fire support platform. The base configuration mounts ten Ultra Autocannon/2s, providing an extraordinary volume of fire at extreme ranges that few opponents can match. This arsenal allows the Bane to stand off at distance and pepper targets with impunity, though its four ammunition bins limit the duration of sustained engagements. Four machine guns provide a deterrent against infantry and unarmored targets that manage to close inside minimum autocannon range.</p><p>A 300-rated XL engine propels this hundred-ton chassis to a respectable 54 kph, adequate for maintaining position in a defensive line. Nineteen tons of Forging C745 armor provides excellent protection for a second-line design, ensuring the Bane can absorb considerable punishment while delivering its withering long-range fire. Ten double heat sinks manage the design's modest heat output with ease.</p><p>The primary weakness of the base configuration is its dependency on ammunition and the relatively low individual damage of each autocannon round, making the Bane vulnerable to opponents that close range quickly before its massed fire can achieve cumulative effect.</p>

deployment:<p>Introduced around 3110, this variant returns to the original Bane's emphasis on massed autocannon fire while incorporating newer, lighter weapon technology. Ten ProtoMech-scale AC/2s (five in each arm) recall the original configuration's weapon count while using lighter individual weapons. Four extended-range medium lasers in the right torso provide backup firepower, and all weapons are linked to a targeting computer for enhanced accuracy. An ECM suite and endo-composite structure carry over from the Bane 5, while CASE II protects the six tons of autocannon ammunition distributed across the side torsos. Thirteen double heat sinks manage the thermal load.</p>

history:<p>The Bane's origins trace to an unfinished Star League prototype that was carried into exile during the Exodus. Following Operation Klondike and the consolidation of the Pentagon Worlds, the design was first realized in 2827, entering service as an assault-weight fire support platform across multiple Clan toumans. Early production of the Bane centered on the Ironhold Alpha Complex, where the design was manufactured under Clan Jade Falcon ownership from the Late Succession Wars through the Civil War era.</p><p>Throughout its early history, the Bane remained uncommon among Jade Falcon second-line forces due to a lack of standardization and the relative ease of manufacturing competing designs such as the Jupiter. When the Jupiter shifted toward a fast brawler role in the 3090s, Banes filled the resulting heavy fire-support vacancy, becoming more prevalent than before and providing Falcon engineers with additional data for continued development. This longevity, coupled with the Falcon scientists' unusual interest in the platform, contributed to its role as a test bed for experimental technology that often found later application in other BattleMechs.</p><p>The Bane's combat record spans numerous conflicts across the Clan Invasion and beyond. The Bane 4 saw its baptism of fire during Jade Falcon strikes against Lyran forces at Blair Atholl and during subsequent strikes on Pandora between 3064 and 3065, where its close-range firepower caught Lyran defenders off guard. During Operation Noyan in 3147, Banes of the Eighteenth Falcon Regulars held the line against Hell's Horses at the Suleiman Dunes on Leskovik, demonstrating the design's enduring defensive capability.</p><p>Production of the Bane expanded beyond Ironhold to Olivetti Weaponry on Sudeten, which also operated a refit line converting existing chassis to updated specifications. The Bane 4 was additionally produced at the Tokasha MechWorks Alpha facility under successive Clan ownership, Ghost Bear, then Hell's Horses, and later Clan Stone Lion. The Olivetti facility suffered damage during the Wars of Reaving era but restored Bane production in the late 3090s, becoming the primary source of new Bane manufacture from the Dark Age onward.</p><p>The introduction of the modernized Bane 5, 6, and 7 variants from Olivetti Weaponry between 3105 and 3122 ensured the design's continued relevance well into the ilClan era, a remarkable testament to the adaptability of a chassis first conceived before the founding of the Clans themselves.</p>

